ilterStrategy());\n42:         }\n43:         config.setTopic(remaining);\n44:         config.setServers(servers);\n45:         config.setVerbose(verbose);\n46: \n47:         if (config.getSslContextParameters() == null) {\n48:             config.setSslContextParameters(retrieveGlobalSslContextParameters());\n49:         }\n50: \n51:         NatsEndpoint answer = new NatsEndpoint(uri, this, config);\n52:         setProperties(answer, parameters);\n53:         return answer;\n54:     }\n55: \n56:     /**\n57:      * URLs to one or more NAT servers. Use comma to separate URLs when specifying multiple servers.\n58:      */\n59:     public String getServers() {\n60:         return servers;\n61:     }\n62: \n63:     public void setServers(String servers) {\n64:         this.servers = servers;\n65:     }\n66: \n67:     @Override\n68:     public boolean isUseGlobalSslContextParameters() {\n69:         return this.useGlobalSslContextParameters;\n70:     }\n71: \n72:     /**\n73:      * Enable usage of global SSL context parameters.\n74:      */\n75:     @Override\n76:     public void setUseGlobalSslContextParameters(boolean useGlobalSslContextParameters) {\n77:         this.useGlobalSslContextParameters = useGlobalSslContextParameters;\n78:     }\n79: \n80:     public boolean isVerbose() {\n81:         return verbose;\n82:     }\n83: \n84:     /**\n85:      * Whether or not running in verbose mode\n86:      */\n87:     public void setVerbose(boolean verbose) {\n88:         this.verbose = verbose;\n89:     }\n90: }\n91: ","url":"https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/github.com/sg-evals/camel--1006f047@0c671f6f3a67e1d63502e00ea42b10fc10c15a57/-/blob/components/camel-nats/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/nats/NatsComponent.java"}", "annotations": null, "meta": null}], "structuredContent": {"content": "1: /*
